# WHAT IT IS
#   bsky is "a cli application for bluesky social" — mattn's
#   Go-native command-line client for Bluesky / the AT Protocol.
#   Built on top of the official bluesky-social/indigo Go SDK,
#   it exposes a comprehensive surface for everything you can
#   do in the Bluesky web app:  show profiles, view and stream
#   the timeline, post + delete + repost + vote, follow /
#   unfollow / block / unblock / mute / unmute, manage lists +
#   moderation lists, app passwords + invite codes, search
#   posts and actors, run a NIP-46-style chat session via the
#   `chat` subcommand, and even act as an MCP server for AI
#   agents via the `mcp` subcommand.  Profile state lives in
#   `~/.config/bsky/<profile>.json` (multi-profile via the
#   `-a` global flag).
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from main.go urfave/cli/v2
#                       cli.App `Commands: []*cli.Command{...}`
#                       chain; extracted via `gh api repos/
#                       mattn/bsky/contents/main.go`)
#
#   bsky [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Global options:
#     -a <PROFILE>                   Profile name  (selects
#                                    which `~/.config/bsky/
#                                    <PROFILE>.json` to load)
#     -V                             Verbose mode
#
#   Subcommands  (with notable per-subcommand flags):
#     login                          Authenticate against a PDS
#                                    and persist the session
#
#     show-profile                   Show a profile
#       -H, --handle <HANDLE>          User handle  (defaults
#                                      to logged-in account)
#       --json                         Output JSON
#     update-profile [DISPLAY-NAME [DESCRIPTION]]
#                                    Update your profile
#       --avatar <FILE>                Avatar image file
#       --banner <FILE>                Banner image file
#     show-session                   Show the current session
#       --json
#
#     timeline (tl)                  Show your home timeline
#       -H, --handle <HANDLE>
#       -n <N>                         Number of items
#                                      [default: 30]
#       --json
#     stream                         Stream the firehose
#       --cursor <CURSOR>
#       -H, --handle <HANDLE>
#       --pattern <REGEX>              Content pattern filter
#       --reply <ID>                   Filter replies of event
#       --json
#     thread <URL|ID>                Show a thread
#       -n <N>                         Number of items
#                                      [default: 30]
#       --json
#     search <QUERY>                 Search posts
#     search-actors <QUERY>          Search actors
#     notification                   Show notifications
#       --json
#
#   Status authoring:
#     post [TEXT...]                 Publish a post (text from
#                                    args, --stdin, or both)
#       -r <URL|ID>                    Reply to URL or post id
#       -q <URL|ID>                    Quote-repost URL or
#                                      post id
#       --stdin                        Read content from stdin
#       -i, --image <FILE>             Attach an image
#                                      (repeatable)
#       --ia, --image-alt <TEXT>       Alt text for the
#                                      corresponding image
#                                      (repeatable)
#       -v, --video <FILE>             Attach a video
#       --va, --video-alt <TEXT>       Alt text for the video
#     delete <URL|ID>                Delete a post / record
#     vote <URL|ID>                  Like a post
#       --down                         Cast a down-vote
#                                      (legacy)
#     votes <URL|ID>                 List likes for a post
#       --json
#     repost <URL|ID>                Repost a post
#     reposts <URL|ID>               List reposts for a post
#       --json
#
#   Social graph:
#     follow <HANDLE>                Follow an account
#     unfollow <HANDLE>              Unfollow an account
#     follows                        List who you follow
#       -H, --handle <HANDLE>
#       --json
#     followers                      List who follows you
#       -H, --handle <HANDLE>
#       --json
#     block <HANDLE>                 Block an account
#     unblock <HANDLE>               Unblock an account
#     blocks                         List blocked accounts
#       --json
#     mute <HANDLE>                  Mute an account
#     unmute <HANDLE>                Unmute an account
#     mutes                          List muted accounts
#       --json
#
#   Lists + moderation:
#     list                           List your lists / show
#                                    members of a list
#     lists                          List all lists you own
#     moderation-list                Manage moderation lists
#     report <URL|ID>                Submit a moderation report
#
#   App passwords + invite codes:
#     add-app-password <NAME>        Generate a new app password
#     list-app-passwords             List your app passwords
#     revoke-app-password <NAME>     Revoke an app password
#     invite-codes                   List invite codes (issued
#                                    + used)
#
#   Chat + MCP:
#     chat                           Open an interactive chat
#                                    REPL against a Bluesky DM
#                                    conversation
#     mcp                            Run as an MCP server for
#                                    AI agents  (Model Context
#                                    Protocol)
#
#   Standard urfave/cli auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help (root + each
#                                    subcommand)
#     -v, --version                  Show version
#
#   Bash completion is enabled (`EnableBashCompletion: true`),
#   so `bsky` also speaks the urfave/cli completion protocol
#   under bash.
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/bluesky-social/indigo
#   v0.0.0-20260318...` declared in go.mod (pseudo-version
#   pinning the master branch) — `indigo` is THE canonical
#   reference Go implementation of the AT Protocol, maintained
#   directly by Bluesky-the-company (bluesky-social/indigo,
#   2,700+ stars; the toolkit that powers the official Bluesky
#   relay (formerly known as BGS), the official `goat` AT
#   protocol CLI (bluesky-social/goat — already covered as
#   `_goat`), the `palomar` search infra, the `hepa` rules
#   engine, the `bigsky` indexer, and every other Bluesky
#   first-party Go service plus dozens of third-party Go
#   ATProto applications — mattn/bsky, jazware/atproto.tools,
#   FiloSottile/mostly-harmless, haileyok/dontshowmethis,
#   furrylist/bsky-furry-feed, CharlesDardaman/blueskyfirehose,
#   did-method-plc/go-didplc, mazrean/skills-pkg, and many
